sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: Peripheral blood mononuclear cell (PBMC) isolation by Ficoll gradient, followed by magnetic activated cell sorting (MACS) of given CD4 T cell sub-populations as follows. Naive, total (bulk) and memory CD4 T cells were isolated in parallel by negative magnetic isolation according to the manufacturer's protocol (Miltenyi Biotec). From an aliquot of total CD4 T cells, GM-CSF producing and GM-CSF negative cells were subsequently isolated without restimulation using the GM-CSF Secretion Assay - Cell  ...
sample_growth_protocol_ch1: Primary cells from human peripheral blood.
sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Nuclear isolation was carried out according to Buenrostro et al. 2013 (PMID: 24097267)., Library construction including tagmentation and PCR amplification was performed according to Buenrostro et al. 2013 (PMID: 24097267) followed by additional gel size selection of DNA in the size range of 150-230 base pairs.
sample_data_processing: Base-calling was performed using Illumina HiSeq Control/Real Time Analysis software., Base-call files were demultiplexed and converted to fastq files using bcl2fastq version 2.17.1.14., Fastq files were adapter-trimmed using scythe version 0.991 and quality-trimmed using sickle version 1.33., Trimmed fastq files were aligned to the human genome version hg38 using bowtie version 2.3.0 with the ‘--very-sensitive’ setting., Bam files were sorted, indexed and filtered using samtools version 0.1.19 t ...
supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab delimited text file containing read counts at reproducibly accessible genomic regions (consensus peaks)

sample_data_processing: Base-calling was performed using Illumina HiSeq Control/Real Time Analysis software., Base-call files were demultiplexed and converted to fastq files using bcl2fastq version 2.17.1.14., Fastq files were adapter-trimmed using scythe version 0.991 and quality-trimmed using sickle version 1.33., Trimmed fastq files were aligned to the human genome version hg38 using bowtie version 2.3.0 with the ‘--very-sensitive’ setting., Bam files were sorted, indexed and filtered using samtools version 0.1.19 t ...
supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab delimited text file containing read counts at reproducibly accessible genomic regions (consensus peaks)

sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: Peripheral blood mononuclear cell (PBMC) isolation by Ficoll gradient, followed by magnetic activated cell sorting (MACS) of given CD4 T cell sub-populations as follows. Naive, total (bulk) and memory CD4 T cells were isolated in parallel by negative magnetic isolation according to the manufacturer's protocol (Miltenyi Biotec). From an aliquot of total CD4 T cells, GM-CSF producing and GM-CSF negative cells were subsequently isolated without restimulation using the GM-CSF Secretion Assay - Cell  ...

sample_data_processing: Base-calling was performed using Illumina HiSeq Control/Real Time Analysis software., Base-call files were demultiplexed and converted to fastq files using bcl2fastq version 2.17.1.14., Fastq files were adapter-trimmed using scythe version 0.991 and quality-trimmed using sickle version 1.33., Trimmed fastq files were aligned to the human genome version hg38 using bowtie version 2.3.0 with the ‘--very-sensitive’ setting., Bam files were sorted, indexed and filtered using samtools version 0.1.19 t ...
supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab delimited text file containing read counts at reproducibly accessible genomic regions (consensus peaks)

sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: Peripheral blood mononuclear cell (PBMC) isolation by Ficoll gradient, followed by magnetic activated cell sorting (MACS) of given CD4 T cell sub-populations as follows. Naive, total (bulk) and memory CD4 T cells were isolated in parallel by negative magnetic isolation according to the manufacturer's protocol (Miltenyi Biotec). From an aliquot of total CD4 T cells, GM-CSF producing and GM-CSF negative cells were subsequently isolated without restimulation using the GM-CSF Secretion Assay - Cell  ...

sample_data_processing: Base-calling was performed using Illumina HiSeq Control/Real Time Analysis software., Base-call files were demultiplexed and converted to fastq files using bcl2fastq version 2.17.1.14., Fastq files were adapter-trimmed using scythe version 0.991 and quality-trimmed using sickle version 1.33., Trimmed fastq files were aligned to the human genome version hg38 using bowtie version 2.3.0 with the ‘--very-sensitive’ setting., Bam files were sorted, indexed and filtered using samtools version 0.1.19 t ...
supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab delimited text file containing read counts at reproducibly accessible genomic regions (consensus peaks)

sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: Peripheral blood mononuclear cell (PBMC) isolation by Ficoll gradient, followed by magnetic activated cell sorting (MACS) of given CD4 T cell sub-populations as follows. Naive, total (bulk) and memory CD4 T cells were isolated in parallel by negative magnetic isolation according to the manufacturer's protocol (Miltenyi Biotec). From an aliquot of total CD4 T cells, GM-CSF producing and GM-CSF negative cells were subsequently isolated without restimulation using the GM-CSF Secretion Assay - Cell  ...

sample_data_processing: Base-calling was performed using Illumina HiSeq Control/Real Time Analysis software., Base-call files were demultiplexed and converted to fastq files using bcl2fastq version 2.17.1.14., Fastq files were adapter-trimmed using scythe version 0.991 and quality-trimmed using sickle version 1.33., Trimmed fastq files were aligned to the human genome version hg38 using bowtie version 2.3.0 with the ‘--very-sensitive’ setting., Bam files were sorted, indexed and filtered using samtools version 0.1.19 t ...
supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab delimited text file containing read counts at reproducibly accessible genomic regions (consensus peaks)

sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: Peripheral blood mononuclear cell (PBMC) isolation by Ficoll gradient, followed by magnetic activated cell sorting (MACS) of given CD4 T cell sub-populations as follows. Naive, total (bulk) and memory CD4 T cells were isolated in parallel by negative magnetic isolation according to the manufacturer's protocol (Miltenyi Biotec). From an aliquot of total CD4 T cells, GM-CSF producing and GM-CSF negative cells were subsequently isolated without restimulation using the GM-CSF Secretion Assay - Cell  ...

sample_growth_protocol_ch1: Primary cells from human peripheral blood.
sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Cells were washed with PBS and lysed in QIAzol Lysis Reagent (Qiagen) by vortexing and incubating for 5 min at 20°C. Lysates were stored at -80°C until RNA extraction. RNA was extracted with the miRNeasy Micro Kit (Qiagen) according to the manufacturer’s instructions. RNA concentration was determined on a Nanodrop 2000 spectrophotometer (Thermo Fisher Scientific) and RNA quality was controlled on a 2100 Bioanalyzer instrument (Agilent Technologies) using an Agilent RNA 6000 Pico Kit. RNA integri ...
sample_data_processing: Base-calling was performed using Illumina HiSeq Control/Real Time Analysis software., Base-call files were demultiplexed and converted to fastq files using bcl2fastq version 2.17.1.14., Sequence reads were aligned to the human genome version hg38 using STAR version 2.5.2b with the GENCODE version 25 annotation file and with the settings ‘--clip3pAdapterSeq <adapters>’ for adapter trimming and ‘--quantMode  TranscriptomeSAM GeneCounts’ for counting read pairs on the gene level.
supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab delimited text file containing counts of read pairs for GENCODE version 25 genes
